The paper involves the use of deep reinforcement learning (RL) architecture for portfolio optimization, which falls under the category of machine learning. The paper also mentions the use of a prediction module, data augmentation module, and behavior cloning module, which are commonly used in deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ML (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of real-time interaction and simulation, which could fall under the category of cs.TR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Finally, the paper involves the use of historical financial market data, which could fall under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
